1
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:15,633
Get back in the car.

2
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:16,700
Don't look at this ugly person.

3
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:18,100
I don't want my grandchild
to become ugly.

4
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:19,233
Please just get back in the car.

5
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:21,900
I'm amazed by how you were
taking care of Eden.

6
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:24,467
And not all mother-in-laws
are like you.

7
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:26,633
Thank you, Auntie.

8
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,700
I owe you all of this.

9
00:00:28,767 --> 00:00:33,600
I told you I am better
than your mother.

10
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,000
This is all your fault!

11
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:36,633
You and your brother!

12
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:38,833
This is what you call karma.

13
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:41,433
Eden almost lost her baby.

14
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:45,133
Eden will never forgive you.

15
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,500
If I were you...

16
00:00:46,567 --> 00:00:49,667
I'd cross the road and get hit
by a car!

17
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:51,400
Go kill yourself, Amanda!

18
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:55,733
Where have you been?

19
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,567
I just picked this up.

20
00:00:57,633 --> 00:01:00,933
When our plane crashed,
I thought I'd lost everything.

21
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,300
But when I found you...

22
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:03,533
I got to know you...

23
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:06,833
from then on, I knew we were
meant to be together.

24
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,200
Will you marry me?

25
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:09,300
Yes.

26
00:01:09,367 --> 00:01:11,333
Congratulations!

27
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,467
Congratulations!

28
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:14,533
We were celebrating earlier,

29
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:16,233
and now you're giving me
that look.

30
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:19,267
I was just letting
your son get his way.

31
00:01:19,333 --> 00:01:21,000
Because I don't want him
to feel sad,

32
00:01:21,067 --> 00:01:23,767
and I don't want to lose him.

33
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:28,133
But honestly, even if Eden
carries our grandchild,

34
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:31,333
do you think I can accept her?

35
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,467
I'm always
praying for her.

36
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:35,800
I hope nothing bad happened
to her.

37
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:37,800
It's all my fault.

38
00:01:37,867 --> 00:01:39,400
Miss, don't kill yourself!

39
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:40,600
You don't know
anything about me!

40
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:41,967
You don't know me.

41
00:01:46,267 --> 00:01:50,233
When I left, I thought
I'd forget about you.

42
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:51,433
But I was wrong, Amanda.

43
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:54,400
I'm still in love with you.

44
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,533
Who would have thought...

45
00:02:01,267 --> 00:02:02,700
I'd see you again?

46
00:02:06,867 --> 00:02:08,233
Where am I?

47
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,300
Please, don't hurt me.

48
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:15,767
Don't be scared.

49
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,167
I won't hurt you.

50
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:20,033
Amanda, it's me, Lucho.

51
00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:25,433
Please, don't hurt me.

52
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,767
Don't you remember me?

53
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:35,900
No one will hurt you here.

54
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:37,733
No one.

55
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,233
You're safe here, Amanda.

56
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,767
No one will hurt you.

57
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,800
Amanda...

58
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,167
look at me.

59
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:08,167
It's me, Lucho.

60
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,600
I'm your friend.

61
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:28,500
Amanda.

62
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:32,100
Lucho.

63
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,367
Lucho.

64
00:03:38,267 --> 00:03:39,267
How are you?

65
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:43,333
Aren't you tired
of following me around?

66
00:03:45,533 --> 00:03:48,833
I already told you I couldn't
return your feelings.

67
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,167
Amanda, I love you.

68
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:57,567
Why don't you try to love again?

69
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:03,467
Nothing's wrong with it
because you're now a widow.

70
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:11,900
Don't you want your child
to have a family?

71
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:17,700
I can raise my child on my own.

72
00:04:17,767 --> 00:04:20,733
A lot of women out there
can raise their children

73
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,333
on their own.

74
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:31,300
But it's better if your child
will grow up with both parents.

75
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,700
Don't worry.

76
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:35,433
I accept your situation.

77
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:41,033
I will love your child
as my own.

78
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,500
I won't leave you.

79
00:04:44,267 --> 00:04:47,200
I won't abandon you
like your husband.

80
00:04:48,933 --> 00:04:50,700
That's how much I love you,
Amanda.

81
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,700
I will help you out.

82
00:04:57,633 --> 00:05:01,100
Amanda, I hope you can give me
a chance.

83
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:04,733
Sorry, Lucho.

84
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:09,433
I don't want to fool you.

85
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,700
You're a good person...

86
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:17,033
but I don't love you.

87
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:23,433
I don't want to take advantage
of your feelings for me.

88
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:28,767
I'm sorry.

89
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:05,733
Goodbye, Amanda.

90
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,400
I'll just leave this place.

91
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:14,267
You can't love me anyway.

92
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:19,600
I hope I can forget you
once I leave this place.

93
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:29,700
Lucho?

94
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:46,567
Goodnight, Auntie.

95
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:49,867
Eden, wait.

96
00:06:49,933 --> 00:06:52,133
I want to talk to you.

97
00:06:53,667 --> 00:06:56,000
Okay, what is it about?

98
00:06:56,067 --> 00:07:01,100
You know you're no stranger
to us.

99
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:04,167
You're a part of our family.

100
00:07:04,233 --> 00:07:11,767
I want to give you
a lavish wedding.

101
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,100
Thank you, Auntie.

102
00:07:13,167 --> 00:07:15,900
Red will be happy
to hear that.

103
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:22,500
But let's not rush your wedding,
if that's okay.

104
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:26,300
Because you're pregnant already.

105
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:30,900
And soon, your pregnancy
will be noticeable.

106
00:07:30,967 --> 00:07:34,033
I don't want other people
to talk against you.

107
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,500
You know what I mean.

108
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:37,600
I will be the first one
to get hurt.

109
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:40,567
I don't want them to talk like
that about you.

110
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:45,333
They might say you're indecent.

111
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,467
That you're a flirt.

112
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:50,300
That you got pregnant before
marriage.

113
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,600
I don't want that to happen,
okay?

114
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:54,400
I just want to protect you.

115
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:58,300
I understand.

116
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:00,867
Good.

117
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:05,667
So I hope you can talk sense
into Red.

118
00:08:05,733 --> 00:08:10,200
Try to convince him not to get
married right now.

119
00:08:10,267 --> 00:08:12,900
I don't want us to fight.

120
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:15,800
You know how he is.

121
00:08:15,867 --> 00:08:19,533
Maybe you can get married
after giving birth,

122
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:22,867
but not right now. Okay?

123
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,600
Okay, go ahead.

124
00:08:27,667 --> 00:08:30,367
Get some rest for now.

125
00:08:30,433 --> 00:08:32,733
You, too.

126
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:45,400
No, I disagree with that.

127
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:49,700
Red.

128
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,833
Do you agree with my mom?

129
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,067
Hear me out first, please.

130
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:56,300
Your mom is right.

131
00:08:56,400 --> 00:09:02,267
She's just protecting us
from judgmental people.

132
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:06,233
I don't want other people
to talk about us, either.

133
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:10,067
And I want to fix my
relationship with my mom first.

134
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:12,867
I want them to be
at our wedding.

135
00:09:17,267 --> 00:09:20,100
I have nothing against that.

136
00:09:20,167 --> 00:09:23,400
It's just that we've already
talked about this.

137
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:24,433
I know.

138
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:28,067
But we don't have to rush
the wedding.

139
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:30,300
I only want to grant
your mom's wish

140
00:09:30,367 --> 00:09:33,900
to give us a beautiful wedding.

141
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:36,700
And I want everyone
at our wedding.

142
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:38,100
Right?

143
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:44,300
Are you sure that's
the only reason?

144
00:09:44,367 --> 00:09:47,833
Fine, I admit.

145
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:51,433
I don't want you to fight
with your mom.

146
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,400
My mom and I are already
not in good terms.

147
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,333
I don't want that to happen
to you and your mom.

148
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:58,400
I don't want to cause
your family any trouble.

149
00:09:58,467 --> 00:09:59,633
Come on, Red. Please.

150
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,667
Let's do what your mom says.

151
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:03,333
She has a good reason, anyway.

152
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:07,600
She only wants the best for us.

153
00:10:07,667 --> 00:10:09,133
Please.

154
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:12,233
Okay, fine.

155
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:15,033
Let's postpone the wedding
for now.

156
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:17,167
I'll do it for you.

157
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:41,700
Amanda.

158
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:46,600
What were you planning to do
when I saw you on the road?

159
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:50,367
Why do you want to end
your life?

160
00:10:56,300 --> 00:11:01,133
How does it feel to get disowned
by your own daughter?

161
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:09,167
This is it, Amanda.

162
00:11:09,267 --> 00:11:13,133
This will be your new home.

163
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:22,167
Why do you want to end
your life?

164
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:26,167
What pushed you to do that?

165
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,633
Because of those monsters!

166
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:44,467
They ruined my life.

167
00:11:48,433 --> 00:11:51,733
They tore me apart.

168
00:12:03,367 --> 00:12:04,533
Don't cry.

169
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:08,167
They can't hurt you anymore.

170
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:09,567
I'm here now.

171
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:12,267
I will never leave you.

172
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:15,400
I will help you.

173
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:45,700
Auntie, how are you?

174
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:48,300
I just got home from Cebu.

175
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:51,133
Your mom hasn't come home yet.

176
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:54,833
What? Did she leave?

177
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:57,300
She still has her belongings
here.

178
00:12:57,367 --> 00:12:59,333
I wonder where she is.

179
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:06,400
What if something
happened to her?

180
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:08,400
I hope not.

181
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:09,667
Don't think negatively.

182
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:12,233
It might affect your baby.

183
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:15,067
Don't worry, I'll look for her.

184
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:18,433
Perhaps she's staying with
our distant relatives.

185
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:21,667
She probably just needs time
to think.

186
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:24,567
Red has already proposed.

187
00:13:25,967 --> 00:13:27,567
That's awesome!

188
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:31,533
Are you getting married?

189
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:35,700
I want to reconcile with my mom
first before I get married.

190
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:38,867
So you can be with me.

191
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:40,800
I want our whole family
to be at my wedding.

192
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:41,967
That's right.

193
00:13:42,033 --> 00:13:45,500
I hope she'll come home soon,
so you two can talk.

194
00:13:45,567 --> 00:13:48,600
I'm excited to see you
walk down the aisle.

195
00:13:48,667 --> 00:13:50,400
I feel like it's only yesterday
when I was taking care of you.

196
00:13:50,467 --> 00:13:53,633
I can't believe you're getting
married soon.

197
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:56,633
You'll be married before me.

198
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:59,267
But I'm so happy for you.

199
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:01,200
Thank you, Auntie.

200
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:03,467
I got to go. Take care.

201
00:14:03,533 --> 00:14:06,467
Let me know when you hear
from my mom.

202
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:10,533
I hope nothing bad happened
to her.

203
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:13,900
Thank you, Aunt Dindi.
Take care.

204
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:16,233
Bye.

205
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:18,867
What are you doing over there?

206
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:21,500
Are you hiding?

207
00:14:21,567 --> 00:14:23,833
Who were you talking to?

208
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:28,133
I was talking to Aunt Dindi.

209
00:14:28,233 --> 00:14:30,833
I just asked how she was doing.

210
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:32,500
Were you asking her
how she's doing?

211
00:14:32,567 --> 00:14:35,167
Or your mom?

212
00:14:35,233 --> 00:14:37,367
Why do you need to hide?

213
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:42,033
I couldn't find a signal.

214
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:48,333
My family is wealthy.

215
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:53,000
The whole house has a signal
booster.

216
00:14:53,067 --> 00:14:59,933
You'll get a signal even if
you call someone under a well.

217
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,267
I'm sorry.

218
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:05,433
I have no idea.

219
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,367
Excuse me.

220
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,033
I'll take care of you, Yenyen.

221
00:15:19,433 --> 00:15:22,500
I'll be by your side
until we fix everything.

222
00:15:24,133 --> 00:15:29,567
Until we correct everything
that others think we did wrong.

223
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:31,500
Things that for your mom
are wrong.

224
00:15:32,933 --> 00:15:34,067
Thank you.

225
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,633
Don't ever think
we made a mistake

226
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,933
by choosing to protect our baby.

227
00:15:42,467 --> 00:15:46,267
We have to focus on our baby
for now.

228
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:51,000
Who knows? Our child might fix
everything with our family.

229
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:06,133
Red.

230
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,433
Mom.

231
00:16:08,533 --> 00:16:10,800
I just wanted to check on Eden.

232
00:16:13,433 --> 00:16:16,567
Okay, I'm just going to get
something to eat.

233
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:24,933
Auntie.

234
00:16:28,167 --> 00:16:30,767
I'm sorry.

235
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:33,733
I just overheard
your conversation.

236
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:40,367
Red is right, Eden.

237
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:46,700
Your baby should be
your priority now.

238
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:50,767
Amanda...

239
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:56,733
has put your life and your
baby's life in danger.

240
00:16:58,567 --> 00:17:01,100
You don't need that kind
of stress right now.

241
00:17:02,667 --> 00:17:04,600
I've made a decision, Auntie.

242
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,667
I won't see my mom anymore.

243
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:14,967
It hurts, but it will
be better that way.

244
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:17,800
Right now,

245
00:17:17,867 --> 00:17:20,800
I have to prioritize Red
and my baby.

246
00:17:22,567 --> 00:17:25,200
I'm just afraid of what
she'll think.

247
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:31,967
I don't want her to think
that I hate her.

248
00:17:32,033 --> 00:17:35,033
I don't want to lose my mom.

249
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:38,333
I'm afraid that...

250
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:45,700
I can't bear to think I lost
my mom because of what happened.

251
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:55,600
But, Auntie,
after I gave birth...

252
00:17:55,667 --> 00:17:59,467
and I'm ready to face my mom,
I will talk to her.

253
00:17:59,533 --> 00:18:03,100
I can't bear to lose my mom.

254
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:05,333
I can't do it.

255
00:18:07,733 --> 00:18:09,567
But you're right.

256
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:15,567
I need to prioritize my baby
and Red for now.

257
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:42,733
Red, are you busy?

258
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:45,533
Not really. Why?

259
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:47,233
Is there something wrong?

260
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:49,367
No, I'm okay.

261
00:18:50,133 --> 00:18:53,567
I just want to ask you a favor.

262
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:57,867
Since the baby and I
are stable now...

263
00:18:57,967 --> 00:19:00,200
can we go and look for my mom?

264
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,867
Red, please.

265
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:10,300
I can't have peace of mind,
not until I find her.

266
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:15,700
We're not on good terms,
but she's still my mom.

267
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:16,800
I can't stand
not seeing her.

268
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,033
Please?

269
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,633
Where are we going
to look for her?

270
00:19:27,067 --> 00:19:28,867
I don't know.

271
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:33,667
But I don't want to stay here,
doing nothing.

272
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:36,300
Something bad might
already have happened to her.

273
00:19:36,367 --> 00:19:39,933
She still hasn't come home.

274
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,700
I will feel guilty if something
unpleasant happens to her.

275
00:19:42,767 --> 00:19:44,600
I can't bear it.

276
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:47,733
Red, please, let's find her.

277
00:19:49,067 --> 00:19:50,067
Please.

278
00:19:50,133 --> 00:19:51,467
Please, let's find her.

279
00:19:51,533 --> 00:19:53,267
Okay, fine.

280
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:54,300
We'll find her.

281
00:19:54,367 --> 00:19:57,333
I don't care if we have to go
everywhere.

282
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,467
Thank you.

283
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,733
What they did to you was awful.

284
00:23:32,133 --> 00:23:34,067
They put you in jail
even if you're innocent.

285
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:47,900
I wanted to forget everything
that happened

286
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:49,067
when I got out of jail.

287
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:03,833
But destiny put my patience
to the test.

288
00:24:05,300 --> 00:24:08,567
Their son got Eden pregnant.

289
00:24:10,233 --> 00:24:13,467
And she chose her new family
over me.

290
00:24:13,533 --> 00:24:16,700
That's why I'm all alone now.

291
00:24:16,767 --> 00:24:18,967
You'll never be alone, Amanda.

292
00:24:19,033 --> 00:24:20,233
I'm here now.

293
00:24:23,067 --> 00:24:25,233
I'm still fortunate.

294
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:30,867
Of all the people out there,
it was you who rescued me.

295
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,867
What they did to me
is unforgivable.

296
00:24:42,833 --> 00:24:44,600
I'm a human, not garbage.

297
00:24:46,967 --> 00:24:48,767
They can't hurt you anymore,
Amanda.

298
00:24:49,833 --> 00:24:51,333
They will have to face me first.

299
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:55,033
Just tell me your plans...

300
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:58,633
what you want to do to make
yourself feel better.

301
00:24:58,700 --> 00:25:00,467
I will do everything for you.

302
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,367
Everything?

303
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,933
Yes, everything.

304
00:25:07,967 --> 00:25:09,600
What if I want to get revenge?

305
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:21,000
I will help you.

306
00:25:31,367 --> 00:25:32,633
Who is this?

307
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:34,067
No!

308
00:25:34,133 --> 00:25:35,833
Stop it! No!

309
00:25:35,933 --> 00:25:39,233
And I'm so sure that only
one person can do this to us.

310
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:41,633
It's Amanda!
Amanda's behind all of this!

311
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:44,167
She's the only person
who hates our family!

312
00:25:44,233 --> 00:25:46,167
Auntie, what if it's not my mom?

313
00:25:46,233 --> 00:25:48,267
No? Who else would do this?

314
00:25:48,333 --> 00:25:50,067
You will pay, Rina.

315
00:25:50,133 --> 00:25:51,633
I won't leave you alone.

316
00:25:53,067 --> 00:25:55,233
I will make you pay
for everything.

317
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:57,200
You and your evil brother!

318
00:25:57,267 --> 00:26:00,000
I thought you accepted Eden

319
00:26:00,067 --> 00:26:03,033
now that she's about to give
birth.

320
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:04,067
Eden.
